cluster_relations.rel_desc: Twig mimicry is presented as a specific way caterpillars achieve camouflage.
Leaf mimicry is used as a specific form of camouflage.
Biased data is a problematic form or state of the training data used for AI systems.
remarks: Modelled as type/state of training data.

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Opaque AI systems are a subset or characteristic form of AI systems.
remarks: Modeled as subtype relation to capture that opacity characterizes certain AI systems.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject is a more specific subtype, kind, or state of the object within a taxonomic or type hierarchy.
args.justification: All four relations describe a taxonomic or type hierarchy where the subject is a more specific form of the object: twig mimicry and leaf mimicry are specific camouflage strategies; biased data is a problematic form/state of training data; opaque AI systems are a specific kind of AI systems. Normalizing these to a single predicate 'is_subtype_of' yields a consistent hierarchical edge in the KG.

Each relation encodes a taxonomic or type hierarchy where the subject is a more specific subtype, kind, or characteristic state of the object. Grouping them under a shared class 'taxonomic_subtype_relation' captures this family of hierarchical 'is-a' style links.
All four relations describe hierarchical organization (subtype / kind-of / specific form) between subject and object, which belongs in a broad hierarchy-oriented relation group.
